  "text": "The results indicate a negative and statistically insignificant relationship between tax and total debt ratio. The result is contradict with Trade Off theory that suggest that a company chooses how much debt finance and how much equity finance by balancing the costs of financing and the tax benefits. Previous research with the similar finding [CITATION_1] claimed that SMEs are less likely to be profitable and therefore will not benefit from the tax advantage.",
